    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed the required level. One factor (Test conditions) is below required level due to single-condition testing; this is accepted given the COU is explicitly bounded to the ASTM F1717 standard configuration and regulatory precedent supports this approach. UQ was performed via Monte Carlo propagation of material and geometric input uncertainties; all E/uval metrics are within the pre-established acceptance threshold of 1.96. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support the Medium assurance level required for this Class II device at model risk level 3.",
